From 685f2c5ab3e8d1178d7c03563d801fb1840c7385 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sanket Bumb <sanket@yourowncrm.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 11:51:38 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: schedule bands per date, auto-location, mandatory
 fields, UI reshuffle, fast customer search
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Schedule grid location colors — root cause fixed:
- loadWorkingHours() was only ever called once at component init
  (always computing bands for whatever date the page first loaded on),
  never again on date navigation. Bands now recompute every time
  loadSchedule() runs, so navigating to a different date correctly
  shows that date's configured location colors.

Appointment dialog — auto-populate Location:
- New onDateOrResourceChange(): on double-click-to-create or when the
  user changes Resource/Staff or Date, fetches that entity's resource
  schedule, finds the row matching the date's day-of-week AND within
  its effective date range, and applies its location automatically
- Falls back to the Resource/Staff's profile locationId if no
  schedule entry covers that day
- locationManuallySet flag stops auto-population from overriding a
  location the user deliberately picked or cleared

Appointment dialog — mandatory fields:
- Visit Type: added Validators.required
- Location: added explicit check in new validateRequiredFields()
  helper (it's a standalone field driven by a search box, not a
  plain reactive form control, so it needed manual validation)
- Both save() and saveThenOpen() now use validateRequiredFields()

Appointment dialog — field changes:
- Removed the Duration (min) dropdown entirely — duration is still
  derived correctly from Start/End Time and Visit Type selection,
  just without a separate manual override field
- Charge Amount now sits in that freed-up grid slot
- Collect Payment is now an inline button next to Charge Amount
  (replacing the old footer bar) — shows '✓ Paid .xx' once a
  payment is posted in this session, otherwise '💳 Collect Payment'
- collectPayment() saves the appointment first (so charge amount and
  other edits aren't lost) but no longer closes the dialog — it
  stays open so the Paid label can update immediately
- Swapped Date and Resource/Staff field positions — Date now first

Resource Hours — per-day location now mandatory:
- Removed 'All Locations' option entirely from the per-day dropdown
- Empty selection shows a red invalid-field highlight when the day
  is open
- Backend applyRowFields() throws BusinessException if an open day
  has no location assigned
- Frontend saveConfig() validates this before sending the request

Resource Hours — per-config Save button:
- Removed the single global 'Save Hours' button from the page header
- Added an individual Save button inline with each config's Start
  Date / End Date fields
- saveHours() renamed to saveConfig(triggeredIndex) — still sends
  the full rows array (required by the bulk-replace backend
  endpoint) but tracks which card's button shows 'Saving…' via the
  new savingIndex signal

Customer search performance — root cause fixed:
- The JPQL query used LOWER(column) LIKE LOWER('%term%') across 4
  OR'd columns. Leading-wildcard LIKE patterns cannot use standard
  B-tree indexes (idx_cust_name, idx_cust_phone existed but were
  never actually used by this query), forcing a full table scan
  with per-row LOWER() evaluation on every keystroke
- V5 migration adds pg_trgm extension + GIN trigram indexes on
  first_name, last_name, email, phone, plus a composite
  (tenant_id, active) index
- CustomerRepository.search() rewritten as a native query using
  ILIKE instead of LOWER()+LIKE — ILIKE is what the trigram indexes
  are built to accelerate
- Added explicit countQuery for the native paginated query
